title: Grateful Dead Live at Desert Sky Pavilion on 1994-03-06

reviews.review_text: HSF alone worth 4 stars I've only listened to the first set so far.  This show is definitely before the final decline, because Jerry is so freaking ON at the start.  He absolutely nails the transition then delivers torrential volleys of sound all the way through Slipknot! (which well earns its "!" here).  He misses a few notes on the repeat of the transition, but even these are trifling.  The high energy continues throughout the first set.  My only quibbles are that the dropouts ruin Jerry's solo in Let It Grow, and then the big jam is kind of rushed.  So is the ending, where Jerry is on fire and clearly wants to keep playing, but the band forces a stop.
